WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:25.220 align:middle line:90%


00:00:25.220 --> 00:00:26.890 align:middle line:90%
>>I was talking on the phone.

00:00:26.890 --> 00:00:30.330 align:middle line:84%
The lightening came down
the phone, entered my neck.

00:00:30.330 --> 00:00:32.340 align:middle line:90%
It went through my spine.

00:00:32.340 --> 00:00:35.020 align:middle line:10%
Threw me up in the air.

00:00:35.020 --> 00:00:37.760 align:middle line:10%
And there was this
slight buzzing at the ear

00:00:37.760 --> 00:00:40.940 align:middle line:10%
and I felt myself
pop out of the body.

00:00:40.940 --> 00:00:43.936 align:middle line:84%
Then I felt myself
float up to the ceiling.

00:00:43.936 --> 00:00:46.020 align:middle line:84%
And the doctor and the
nurse were in there,

00:00:46.020 --> 00:00:49.150 align:middle line:84%
and he was looking at
me, say, "She's gone.

00:00:49.150 --> 00:00:52.230 align:middle line:90%
She's dead."

00:00:52.230 --> 00:00:55.360 align:middle line:90%
>>And I was taken to hospital.

00:00:55.360 --> 00:00:59.470 align:middle line:84%
Doctors did anything
they could to help me,

00:00:59.470 --> 00:01:03.780 align:middle line:90%
but I was declared dead.

00:01:03.780 --> 00:01:05.930 align:middle line:84%
>>I realized I
was out of my body

00:01:05.930 --> 00:01:09.260 align:middle line:84%
when I was suddenly
looking at the slide.

00:01:09.260 --> 00:01:11.460 align:middle line:84%
>>Out of that light stepped
a most amazing being

00:01:11.460 --> 00:01:13.400 align:middle line:84%
I have ever been
in the presence of.

00:01:13.400 --> 00:01:18.620 align:middle line:10%
>>It was just total
selflessness, understanding,

00:01:18.620 --> 00:01:22.370 align:middle line:10%
kindness, all consuming love.

00:01:22.370 --> 00:01:23.345 align:middle line:10%
Wonderful love!

00:01:23.345 --> 00:01:44.950 align:middle line:90%


00:01:44.950 --> 00:01:50.760 align:middle line:84%
>>After a time in this
light, all of these people

00:01:50.760 --> 00:01:54.300 align:middle line:90%
have to pay a return trip back.

00:01:54.300 --> 00:01:57.240 align:middle line:10%
What they tell us is that the
reason they chose to come back

00:01:57.240 --> 00:02:00.380 align:middle line:10%
was not for themselves,
because for themselves

00:02:00.380 --> 00:02:02.830 align:middle line:10%
they would rather have stayed
with this presence of love.

00:02:02.830 --> 00:02:06.200 align:middle line:90%


00:02:06.200 --> 00:02:10.539 align:middle line:10%
When they do return,
incidentally, then the story

00:02:10.539 --> 00:02:12.520 align:middle line:10%
becomes very interesting
from the point

00:02:12.520 --> 00:02:14.930 align:middle line:10%
of view of human
psychology, because we

00:02:14.930 --> 00:02:18.300 align:middle line:10%
find that these patients
are profoundly changed.

00:02:18.300 --> 00:02:21.730 align:middle line:84%
That they are imbued with a
totally new value structure.

00:02:21.730 --> 00:02:25.690 align:middle line:10%
That whatever in
their lives before,

00:02:25.690 --> 00:02:30.680 align:middle line:10%
they had been chasing, whether
it was money or power or fame

00:02:30.680 --> 00:02:33.760 align:middle line:10%
or any of these other
things that people seek,

00:02:33.760 --> 00:02:36.140 align:middle line:10%
they say that after
this experience,

00:02:36.140 --> 00:02:41.100 align:middle line:10%
their value primarily
is to love others,

00:02:41.100 --> 00:02:45.810 align:middle line:10%
to seek loving relationships
with their fellow human being.

00:02:45.810 --> 00:02:47.310 align:middle line:10%
And also they tell
us that they have

00:02:47.310 --> 00:02:48.685 align:middle line:10%
no more fear of
death whatsoever.

00:02:48.685 --> 00:03:16.978 align:middle line:90%


00:03:16.978 --> 00:03:19.966 align:middle line:90%
[PHONE RINGING]

00:03:19.966 --> 00:03:24.361 align:middle line:90%


00:03:24.361 --> 00:03:25.444 align:middle line:90%
>>The phone just went off.

00:03:25.444 --> 00:03:28.000 align:middle line:90%


00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:29.210 align:middle line:90%
>>Hello?

00:03:29.210 --> 00:03:29.910 align:middle line:90%
Oh, hey mom.

00:03:29.910 --> 00:03:31.850 align:middle line:90%
How are you?

00:03:31.850 --> 00:03:33.730 align:middle line:90%
Oh no, what's a matter?

00:03:33.730 --> 00:03:37.154 align:middle line:90%
What-- what's happened to him?

00:03:37.154 --> 00:03:39.609 align:middle line:90%
Oh no.

00:03:39.609 --> 00:03:42.560 align:middle line:90%
Oh no.

00:03:42.560 --> 00:03:45.540 align:middle line:84%
I was shocked when I
got that phone call,

00:03:45.540 --> 00:03:51.630 align:middle line:84%
one that nobody ever wants or
ever really expects to get.

00:03:51.630 --> 00:03:55.084 align:middle line:84%
There's just so many feelings
that I really want to share.

00:03:55.084 --> 00:03:58.486 align:middle line:90%
I just wanted to be there.

00:03:58.486 --> 00:04:00.416 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:04:00.416 --> 00:04:00.916 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:04:00.916 --> 00:04:05.902 align:middle line:90%
Well, we'll see you soon.

00:04:05.902 --> 00:04:07.798 align:middle line:90%
Mom, I love you.

00:04:07.798 --> 00:04:11.600 align:middle line:90%


00:04:11.600 --> 00:04:14.320 align:middle line:84%
My dad was fighting for
every breath of life,

00:04:14.320 --> 00:04:17.420 align:middle line:90%
and it didn't look very hopeful.

00:04:17.420 --> 00:04:20.070 align:middle line:84%
Even though we lived
600 miles apart,

00:04:20.070 --> 00:04:24.140 align:middle line:84%
and only saw each other
on holidays, at least

00:04:24.140 --> 00:04:26.840 align:middle line:90%
we were on the same planet.

00:04:26.840 --> 00:04:30.470 align:middle line:84%
And we could pick up
the phone and say hello.

00:04:30.470 --> 00:04:32.010 align:middle line:84%
The likelihood of
losing all that

00:04:32.010 --> 00:04:34.275 align:middle line:84%
seemed almost
impossible to grasp.

00:04:34.275 --> 00:04:43.036 align:middle line:90%


00:04:43.036 --> 00:04:44.008 align:middle line:90%
"Dear dad.

00:04:44.008 --> 00:04:47.410 align:middle line:90%


00:04:47.410 --> 00:04:52.440 align:middle line:84%
I'm so sorry to hear about
what you're going through.

00:04:52.440 --> 00:05:05.005 align:middle line:84%
I know you're rugged, but
you gave us a good scare."

00:05:05.005 --> 00:05:08.070 align:middle line:90%
"Dear dad.

00:05:08.070 --> 00:05:10.370 align:middle line:84%
I'm writing you this
letter because I

00:05:10.370 --> 00:05:12.826 align:middle line:84%
don't know if I'll
ever see you again,

00:05:12.826 --> 00:05:17.280 align:middle line:84%
yet I have so much
I want to say.

00:05:17.280 --> 00:05:19.500 align:middle line:84%
Dad, do you remember
several years

00:05:19.500 --> 00:05:23.860 align:middle line:84%
ago when I was still grieving
over the death of Suzanne?

00:05:23.860 --> 00:05:26.140 align:middle line:84%
I found a great deal of
comfort in some books

00:05:26.140 --> 00:05:29.090 align:middle line:90%
I was reading about dying."

00:05:29.090 --> 00:05:31.762 align:middle line:84%
"It was at that time that I
met a doctor of psychiatry,

00:05:31.762 --> 00:05:35.940 align:middle line:84%
a researcher named
Dr. Raymond Moody.

00:05:35.940 --> 00:05:37.780 align:middle line:84%
I'm sending a copy
of a book that he

00:05:37.780 --> 00:05:43.020 align:middle line:84%
wrote, which was a great
deal of help to me then."

00:05:43.020 --> 00:05:44.940 align:middle line:84%
"Dr. Moody has
observed a pattern

00:05:44.940 --> 00:05:46.780 align:middle line:84%
that occurs in people
the world over,

00:05:46.780 --> 00:05:49.370 align:middle line:84%
regardless of their
culture or religion."

00:05:49.370 --> 00:05:51.670 align:middle line:10%
>>As a matter of fact, the
prior religious beliefs

00:05:51.670 --> 00:05:53.650 align:middle line:10%
or background of
the person doesn't

00:05:53.650 --> 00:05:55.720 align:middle line:10%
seem to have much to
do with whether or not

00:05:55.720 --> 00:05:57.750 align:middle line:10%
they have an
experience, and even

00:05:57.750 --> 00:06:00.850 align:middle line:10%
the content of the experience.

00:06:00.850 --> 00:06:04.770 align:middle line:84%
We've even had people who say
that prior to their experience

00:06:04.770 --> 00:06:07.420 align:middle line:84%
they were atheists
or agnostics who

00:06:07.420 --> 00:06:10.755 align:middle line:84%
have very beautiful and
full-blown near death

00:06:10.755 --> 00:06:11.255 align:middle line:90%
experiences.

00:06:11.255 --> 00:06:11.950 align:middle line:90%
>>Really.

00:06:11.950 --> 00:06:14.210 align:middle line:84%
And do they remain
atheists and agnostics?

00:06:14.210 --> 00:06:14.840 align:middle line:90%
>>Not at all.

00:06:14.840 --> 00:06:17.320 align:middle line:84%
Once they come
back, they tell us

00:06:17.320 --> 00:06:19.970 align:middle line:84%
that they're totally transformed
and they have no more doubt,

00:06:19.970 --> 00:06:22.850 align:middle line:84%
whatsoever that there
is a God and there

00:06:22.850 --> 00:06:25.600 align:middle line:90%
is a life after death.

00:06:25.600 --> 00:06:28.280 align:middle line:84%
>>"It's about his research
on the stories of people

00:06:28.280 --> 00:06:31.130 align:middle line:84%
who have approached
death, many of whom

00:06:31.130 --> 00:06:32.940 align:middle line:84%
actually had the
experience of dying

00:06:32.940 --> 00:06:40.780 align:middle line:84%
and then were revived and
lived to tell about it."

00:06:40.780 --> 00:06:44.480 align:middle line:84%
>>What happened is I felt like
I had been hit by a train.

00:06:44.480 --> 00:06:47.190 align:middle line:10%
But what had happened was
I was talking on the phone,

00:06:47.190 --> 00:06:48.870 align:middle line:10%
holding the telephone like this.

00:06:48.870 --> 00:06:52.594 align:middle line:10%
The lightening came down
the phone, entered my neck.

00:06:52.594 --> 00:06:56.500 align:middle line:84%
It went through my spine,
threw me up in the air.

00:06:56.500 --> 00:06:59.760 align:middle line:84%
As it threw me in the air,
it knocked me out of my shoes

00:06:59.760 --> 00:07:03.350 align:middle line:84%
and welded the nails in the
heels of my shoes to the nails

00:07:03.350 --> 00:07:07.360 align:middle line:84%
in the floor, which is how I was
grounded and I didn't explode.

00:07:07.360 --> 00:07:09.620 align:middle line:10%
>>Before I shot
myself I measured,

00:07:09.620 --> 00:07:14.670 align:middle line:10%
like we did in CPR, to
find where the heart was.

00:07:14.670 --> 00:07:18.005 align:middle line:84%
And that's where I
just took the barrel

00:07:18.005 --> 00:07:20.910 align:middle line:84%
and put it up against my
chest and pulled the trigger.

00:07:20.910 --> 00:07:22.445 align:middle line:90%
>>I had responded to treatment.

00:07:22.445 --> 00:07:25.880 align:middle line:84%
I was getting worse, and
the doctor had come to see.

00:07:25.880 --> 00:07:30.520 align:middle line:10%
And at this point, he
says I've lost her.

00:07:30.520 --> 00:07:32.660 align:middle line:10%
She's gone.

00:07:32.660 --> 00:07:35.100 align:middle line:10%
And I thought, well
who's he talking about?

00:07:35.100 --> 00:07:39.420 align:middle line:84%
Just before this, I had
been in terrible pain.

00:07:39.420 --> 00:07:41.340 align:middle line:90%
I was just hurting so bad.

00:07:41.340 --> 00:07:43.610 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to get away from it.

00:07:43.610 --> 00:07:48.570 align:middle line:10%
>>15 minutes before I was
to be picked up by a jeep,

00:07:48.570 --> 00:07:52.740 align:middle line:10%
I was discovered to have a
temperature of 106 and a half.

00:07:52.740 --> 00:07:54.960 align:middle line:10%
And instead of
waiting for the jeep,

00:07:54.960 --> 00:07:59.290 align:middle line:10%
the captain in charge of the
ward send me over to X-ray.

00:07:59.290 --> 00:08:02.485 align:middle line:84%
And the last thing I remember
was the captain in charge

00:08:02.485 --> 00:08:05.630 align:middle line:84%
of X-ray asked me if I
thought I could sit up

00:08:05.630 --> 00:08:09.424 align:middle line:84%
long enough for them to
get a picture of my chest.

00:08:09.424 --> 00:08:11.090 align:middle line:84%
And I remember hearing
that X-ray making

00:08:11.090 --> 00:08:13.048 align:middle line:84%
that peculiar whirring
sound, and then a click.

00:08:13.048 --> 00:08:15.360 align:middle line:84%
And I'm told that I
collapsed in a heap.

00:08:15.360 --> 00:08:18.440 align:middle line:10%
>>This wasn't a typical
bee sting because I quickly

00:08:18.440 --> 00:08:21.810 align:middle line:10%
realized that there
was a problem.

00:08:21.810 --> 00:08:25.600 align:middle line:10%
And I tried to telephone
someone for help.

00:08:25.600 --> 00:08:29.370 align:middle line:84%
The rest of the ranger station
was about three miles in,

00:08:29.370 --> 00:08:32.520 align:middle line:84%
and I tried to telephone
my boss to send some help.

00:08:32.520 --> 00:08:35.070 align:middle line:90%
And I fell and went unconscious.

00:08:35.070 --> 00:08:37.960 align:middle line:84%
Luckily, from what
I understand, he

00:08:37.960 --> 00:08:40.240 align:middle line:84%
drove through, a bus drove
through a little while

00:08:40.240 --> 00:08:43.169 align:middle line:84%
later and noticed that-- I would
normally just wave to him as he

00:08:43.169 --> 00:08:45.790 align:middle line:84%
came by, and I was
lying down on the floor,

00:08:45.790 --> 00:08:47.270 align:middle line:90%
and he called the ambulance.

00:08:47.270 --> 00:08:53.530 align:middle line:84%
>>I was a dissident
in Soviet Union.

00:08:53.530 --> 00:08:58.340 align:middle line:10%
And I had an invitation
from United States.

00:08:58.340 --> 00:09:01.740 align:middle line:90%


00:09:01.740 --> 00:09:06.330 align:middle line:84%
In 1975 I received
this invitation.

00:09:06.330 --> 00:09:11.190 align:middle line:84%
In 1976 I was given
the exit visa,

00:09:11.190 --> 00:09:16.870 align:middle line:84%
and I was leaving for
New York that day.

00:09:16.870 --> 00:09:21.870 align:middle line:84%
And I was coming to
take my passport,

00:09:21.870 --> 00:09:23.380 align:middle line:90%
and I was ready to fly.

00:09:23.380 --> 00:09:28.910 align:middle line:84%
My family was already in
airport waiting for me.

00:09:28.910 --> 00:09:35.890 align:middle line:84%
The time on sidewalk, I was
moved over or ran over by car.

00:09:35.890 --> 00:09:40.480 align:middle line:90%


00:09:40.480 --> 00:09:44.440 align:middle line:90%
It was fabricated by KGB.

00:09:44.440 --> 00:09:52.130 align:middle line:84%
