00:09:52.130 --> 00:09:57.130 align:middle line:90%
And I was taken to hospital.

00:09:57.130 --> 00:10:02.130 align:middle line:84%
Doctors did anything
they could to help me,

00:10:02.130 --> 00:10:04.820 align:middle line:90%
but I was declared dead.

00:10:04.820 --> 00:10:12.720 align:middle line:90%


00:10:12.720 --> 00:10:17.360 align:middle line:84%
>>Pretty much all over the world
we found this common pattern.

00:10:17.360 --> 00:10:20.650 align:middle line:84%
They tell us that at this
point where their doctor says

00:10:20.650 --> 00:10:23.560 align:middle line:84%
they are dead, that
they may actually

00:10:23.560 --> 00:10:27.040 align:middle line:84%
hear the physician
say, oh my, he's dead,

00:10:27.040 --> 00:10:29.880 align:middle line:84%
or we've lost her or
something like that.

00:10:29.880 --> 00:10:32.110 align:middle line:84%
And they say that from
their perspective, actually,

00:10:32.110 --> 00:10:33.920 align:middle line:90%
they still feel very much alive.

00:10:33.920 --> 00:10:35.645 align:middle line:84%
Indeed their consciousness
is heightened.

00:10:35.645 --> 00:10:36.630 align:middle line:90%
>>Wow.

00:10:36.630 --> 00:10:38.460 align:middle line:84%
>>And they tell
us that they seem

00:10:38.460 --> 00:10:40.280 align:middle line:90%
to leave their physical bodies.

00:10:40.280 --> 00:10:42.940 align:middle line:84%
They say that they
float up, typically

00:10:42.940 --> 00:10:45.900 align:middle line:84%
right above the bed
in the operating

00:10:45.900 --> 00:10:48.590 align:middle line:84%
room, or the emergency
room, and they look down

00:10:48.590 --> 00:10:51.220 align:middle line:84%
and they can see their
own physical bodies

00:10:51.220 --> 00:10:52.870 align:middle line:90%
lying on the bed down below.

00:10:52.870 --> 00:10:53.980 align:middle line:10%
>>I was above my body.

00:10:53.980 --> 00:10:54.932 align:middle line:10%
I was floating.

00:10:54.932 --> 00:10:56.640 align:middle line:84%
And there were people
around me, except I

00:10:56.640 --> 00:11:00.360 align:middle line:84%
didn't realize that that
person there was me.

00:11:00.360 --> 00:11:04.350 align:middle line:84%
>>Then all of a sudden I heard
this statement, he's gone.

00:11:04.350 --> 00:11:05.660 align:middle line:90%
He's gone.

00:11:05.660 --> 00:11:09.080 align:middle line:84%
And it was the paramedic making
that statement to the driver.

00:11:09.080 --> 00:11:12.820 align:middle line:84%
At that point I was standing
behind the paramedic.

00:11:12.820 --> 00:11:15.280 align:middle line:84%
I was watching him
work on my body.

00:11:15.280 --> 00:11:18.920 align:middle line:84%
>>And suddenly there was
commotion beneath me,

00:11:18.920 --> 00:11:23.200 align:middle line:84%
and then I started noticing all
of the people underneath me.

00:11:23.200 --> 00:11:30.150 align:middle line:84%
And the EMS workers were pushing
the stretcher down the hall.

00:11:30.150 --> 00:11:34.720 align:middle line:84%
And I really wasn't
concerned with my body.

00:11:34.720 --> 00:11:37.810 align:middle line:84%
I was more concerned with there
